spans.text: sees her Temples take a swarthy Hue
her Temples take a swarthy Hue
that wearest a gloomy Form , With lowering Forehead , like a northern Storm
comest thou from the Regions of Despair , To shake my Senses with a meagre Stare
when I sigh , and answers to my Tears : Now who shall bow before this withered Shrine , This Mortal Image , that was late Divine
who shall bow before this withered Shrine , This Mortal Image , that was late Divine
Sempronia smooths her wrinkled Brows with Care , And Isabella curls her grizzled Hair :
afraid , Who even trembles at the Name of Maid
not Reason with thy Beauties fly
unload her aching Head Of twisted Papers
Let sage Augusta now , without a Frown , Strip those gay Ribbons from her aged Crown
Let sage Augusta now , without a Frown
the laced Slipper of delicious Hue For a warm Stocking , and an easy Shoe
Guard her swelled Ankles from Rheumatic Pain , And from her Cheek
amongst the Frolic and the Gay

while Ophelia is forbid the Room , Her Mother hobbles in a Rigadoon ; Or to the Sound of melting Music dies , And in their Sockets rolls her blinking Eyes ; Or stuns the Audience with her hideous Squal , While Scorn and Satire whisper through the Hall
